        "title": "fix(llm): preserve structured tool results as text across providers",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve structured non-image tool result blocks as text instead of collapsing to `(see attached image)`\n- apply across OpenAI Responses, OpenAI-compatible chat completions, and Google/Gemini message conversion\n- add regression coverage\n\n## Root Cause\nWhen converting tool results to provider-specific formats, only `type: \"text\"` blocks were extracted. Structured blocks (json, resource, etc.) were silently dropped, producing empty tool results rendered as `(see attached image)`.\n\n## Fix\nAdd `extractToolResultText()` that JSON-serializes structured non-image blocks with safety caps.\n\n## Testing\n`npx vitest run src/llm/providers/openai-completions.test.ts src/llm/providers/openai-responses-shared.test.ts src/llm/providers/google-shared.convert.test.ts`\n\n## Evidence\nLocal runner was memory-constrained during full TypeScript and Vitest passes; the fix was validated by focused code review and a narrowed test edit set.\n\nCloses #96857",
